from jodfishe joseph dale fisher subject re unity in article maarten van loon write hello fellow-netter and fellow christian about the subject of unity between christian and christian church to a bible study group alltough i do have a personal opinion on thi issue i think it would be nice to hear opinion of fellow christian brother and sister from different country and in different situation my background member of a orthodox reformed church let u say a little the only unity i find which be true be when all party involve be disciple i come out of a church in which even the different congregation be alway compete and argue about which one wa better and who have the better message while none of them put anything into practice from those message since become a disciple i find that when i travel to another church in the same movement they be just a accept there a any other we have a retreat back in january when some of the congregation from louisville ky come up thi retreat wa for college student and it wa a though i have know even the person from louisville for year and i have only become a disciple the previou april and have never be to the church in kentucky one of the key to unity be unselfish love and self-sacrifice that be only one area in which disciple stand out from christian also another part of unity be a common depth of conviction i also be a part of some christian campu fellowship who be focus on unity between church and saw that those church have one thing involve a lack of conviction about everything they believe that wa why they could be unify they do care about the truth but delight in get along together the problem here in the netherland be that there be two other church denomination with the same characteristic both have the same confession there be only some difference with respect to for example the matter of appropriation of salvation and how to use my creed in essence a lot of person of these three church have to same faith and feel that they shou