a for those who think about only one church be the true one i remind them that mark state that there be disciple who be not a part of the main group to begin with but they will not lose their reward a with the boston movement i hear numerou time thi exact same thing that there be disciple out there that be not a part of the boston movement but that do not make them any le disciple of course few person admit that they ever run into someone who ha the quality of a disciple outside the movement i know i have maybe thi last problem sound a little strange to most of you for ymy information we have a lot of organization here which be found by person of one specific church and whose member be all member of that church thi ha be consider a correct for year only a few year ago person start to discus about thi and now we be in the middle of thi proces some organization be open their door for person from other church etc i must warn that thi sound cliquey to me a clique be a group which run around together to some extent exclusively thi cause problem in fellowship and cause division i would not say at all that thi be something correct for a to do for any reason in one of the church i attend for example there wa an internal clique of person who be on the different head of the congregation they rarely talk to anyone else outside of the committee and seldom be vote out of office without another office be open up so that they would have to step right back in their degree of exclusion wa such that when the new pastor come he nearly have to wipe out everything and start from scratch i wish he would since they still have no clue about what it mean to be a disciple anyway thi rigidity in the clique be begin to be break down but be still there so i must warn against such division within there enough division without thank for ymy opinion in advance maarten joe fisher 